\begin{frame}{Bisimulation}
Two worlds \HOLtm{w IN M.frame.world} and \HOLtm{v IN N.frame.world} are \emph{bisimilar} (write \HOLtm{bisim_world M N w v})if they 
\begin{itemize}
\item satisfies the same propositional letters.
\item if we can make a transation from one of the worlds, we can make a corresponding transation from the other one.
\end{itemize}

\begin{holmath}
 \HOLthm[w1/w,w2/w',M1/M,M2/M',width=40]{chap2_5.thm_2_62}
\end{holmath}

\end{frame}



\begin{frame}{Reaching out to FOL}
\begin{itemize}
\item John Harrison's previous work in 1998.
\item \HOLtm{feval M σ phi} for satisfaction of \HOLtm{phi} in \HOLtm{M} under the assignment \HOLtm{σ} of free variables.
\item $\mathcal L_{\tau}^1$ formulas
\begin{itemize}
\item no functions (incl. constants)
\item no predicate with arity $\textgreater 2$ 
\item one binary predicate represented by $0$
\item Unary predicates correspond to propositional letters
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\end{frame}

