\begin{frame}{Invariant for bisimulation}
We have \HOLtm{invar4bisim x (:α) (:β) ϕ} if $\phi$ 
\begin{itemize}
\item has no free variable other then $x$.
\item is ${\mathcal L}^1_{\tau}$.
\item once \HOLtm{bisim_world M N w v}, \HOLtm{phi} is satisfied at $w$ iff it is satisfied at $v$.
\end{itemize}

Van Benthem Theorem : `an $\mathcal L_{\tau}^1$ formula is invariant for bisimulation iff it is equivalent to a standard translation'.

\end{frame}

